songs.title: Get Home
songs.lyrics:
[Chorus 1]
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I

[Verse 1]
We are the last people standing
At the end of the night
We are the greatest pretenders
In the cold morning light

[Pre-Chorus]
This is just another night
And we've had many of them
To the morning we're cast out
But I know I'll land here again

[Chorus 1]
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I

[Verse 2]
There's a light in the bedroom
But it's dark
Scattered around on the floor
All my thoughts

[Pre-Chorus]
This is just another night
And we've had many of them
To the morning we're cast out
But I know I'll land here again

[Chorus 2]
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
Oh, how am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I

[Bridge]
The birds are mocking me
They call to be heard
The birds are mocking me
They curse my return

[Chorus 1]
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I

[Outro]
Oh, how am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
Oh, how am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I
How am I gonna get myself back home?
I, I, I

I'm lost...
